CASE073525: Setting up Direct Deposit - Workday Help - Workday - Google Chrome

defaultValue.string:
Thank you for contacting HR Shared Services. All team members are required to use direct deposit to receive their pay. To add or update direct deposit information, please go to the following pathway: Workday profile button (blue cloud or your own photo) > View Profile > Pay > Payment Elections > Add (or Edit, Remove, or View). If you would like to add an additional account, you may click Add under the Accounts section. 

Please note that you will need to make updates end of day on Monday of Payroll week to ensure your information applies for that week’s pay. If your payment election information is changed after Monday evening, it may not take effect until the next pay date depending on when payroll is complete for the current pay cycle. 

Please review the Selecting Your Payment Elections Job Aid in the Workday Resource Hub for step-by-step instructions on how to add or edit your direct deposit information.

Thank you for contacting HR Shared Services. If you have any questions or need assistance regarding your Education Assistance, please contact Bright Horizons directly at 855-853-4980. For information on how to apply, please search for “Education Assistance” in the Workday search bar. The Education Assistance Program article has a link that will take you directly to the Bright Horizons website to review additional information and apply. You may also visit https://aah.edassist.com directly as well.

For additional information regarding this policy, please review the following pathway in WI: Caregiver Connect > My Quick Links > PolicyTech > AAH Education Assistance Program policy and in IL: Advocate Online > Top Applications > Advocate Aurora Document System (AADS)/Policies & Procedures - NEW > AAH Education Assistance Program policy.

Please use the Workday search bar to view additional information in the available articles.

defaultValue.string:
Thank you for contacting HR Shared Services. If you need a replacement badge due to a transfer, incorrect information, building access issues, lost, or worn badge, please follow the best listed option for you below:

WI: Call the IT Helpdesk at 414-647-3520 or submit an online Service Now request through the following pathway: Caregiver Connect > My Quick Links > Service Desk > Service Now.

IL with onsite Public Safety: Speak to your Public Safety Team onsite to request a replacement badge or additional access.

IL with no onsite Public Safety: Your leader should email AMG-IDBadges@aah.org to request a replacement badge (additional information required) or additional access. 

Please use the Workday search bar to view additional information in the available articles.

Thank you for contacting HR Shared Services. Please contact MetLife at 888-294-1988 to begin the process for your leave of absence claim or disability benefit. They will be able to assist you with the application process and answer any questions you may have. 

Please contact MetLife directly:

1. To start a new continuous or non-continuous leave request for yourself or a family member’s health condition

2. To report hours taken for Intermittent non-continuous time taken for an approved FMLA leave

3. To request a Personal (non-medical) leave of absence

MetLife also has a web portal for you to manage and view all your leave of absence communications. This portal is also where you can record any intermittent time taken as well as calling directly.

Contact information:

Phone:  1-888-294-1988, Monday through Friday from 7 am to 10 pm CST

Website:  aahtotalrewards.ehr.com (AAH Benefits Website > Worklife/Leave of Absence)

Please use the Workday search bar to view additional information in the available articles.

***
If you would like more information please respond with the number below corresponding to the information you would like
   1. FMLA Guide
   2. Medical Leave
   3. No further information needed
***
